## StepConfiguration

`StepConfiguration` is a UI pattern used to guide administrators through a multi-step configuration process inside a single settings page.

Whereas the `StepWizard` guides end users through a linear sequence of pages, the StepConfiguration focuses on administrative workflows where:

* All steps are on a single page.
* Steps are visually separated into collapsible boxes.
* Only one step is expanded at a time — the active step.
* Completed steps remain visible but collapsed.
* Users progress by completing the currently expanded step, after which the next one automatically opens.

This makes StepConfiguration ideal for settings pages or multi-part configuration flows where context from previous or future steps should remain visible, without requiring page navigation.

