### When to Use StepConfiguration

Use StepConfiguration when the workflow has these characteristics:

* It is part of an admin configuration section.
* Steps are logically sequential but do not require page transitions.
* The user benefits from having previous and upcoming steps visible at the same time.
* Steps should be grouped into clearly separated sections (cards/boxes).
* Only one section should be interactively open at a time.

Do not use StepConfiguration for user-facing tasks that require focused form completion. For those, use `StepWizard` instead.
